{
  "text": "The charts, clinical notes, and videos of a 10-year consecutive series of 43 patients (23 males and 20 females; age ranging between 22 and 77 years [mean 57]) undergone to an MVD because of an NVCS were retrospectively reviewed. Patients who harbored a hybrid NVCS involving more than a single cranial nerve were excluded from the review. According to the classification scheme proposed by Burchiel [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] TN was classified in Type I, shock-like pain, and Type II, constant pain.",
